            <p>Boston Janry 10. 5650<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                My very dear Doctor<lb/></p>
            <p>Your kind letter recd for which<lb/> accept my most sincere gratitude &#38; thanks<lb/> with reference to our being able to visit your City &#38;<lb/> New York its very doubtful if we can do so inside a<lb/> month&#44; under these circumstance we hereby authorize<lb/> you to order &#38; we will pay the entire <sic>expences</sic> for the<lb/> repairs of the Synagogue in the Russian colony you<lb/> wrote if you will get some reliable contractor even in<lb/> your City to examine the work &#38; send us specifications<lb/> of whats to be done we will liquidate the Bill all<lb/> in memory of my late angel wife my beloved parents &#38;<lb/> my late wife Parents.  With sincere regards in which<lb/> my beloved children join<lb/> Yours most faithfully<lb/> Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
